colombo is a  charter city  with a  mayor council  form of government colombos mayor and the council members are elected through local government elections held once in five years for the past 50 years the city had been ruled by the  united national party  unp a  right  leaning party whose business friendly policies resonate with the population of colombo however the unp nomination list for the 2006 municipal elections was rejected and an independent group supported by the unp won the elections  uvais mohamed imitiyas  was subsequently appointed mayor of colombo
